articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The army-controlled coastal city of Port Sudan has become a refuge from the war raging to the west, but its health system is in near collapse due to power cuts and scarce supplies - and staff shortages now exacerbated by striking doctors.
articles.title: Far from fighting, doctor strikes aggravate healthcare collapse in Port Sudan

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Tests of seawater near Japan's Fukushima nuclear power plant have not detected any radioactivity, the environment ministry said on Sunday, days after authorities began discharging into the sea treated water used to cool damaged reactors.
articles.title: Japan says seawater radioactivity below limits near Fukushima

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russia launched an overnight air attack against Ukraine on Sunday, sending missiles over other northern and central parts of the country, authorities said.
articles.title: Russia launches overnight air attack on northern, central Ukraine

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: UK member of parliament Nadine Dorries has delivered a scathing attack on her Conservative Party's leader Rishi Sunak in her formal resignation letter, accusing the prime minister of running a "zombie parliament" and lacking any political vision.
articles.title: Conservative UK lawmaker formally quits with scathing attack on PM Sunak

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi said there is a risk of a "new model of colonialism" if nations with critical minerals do not regard custodianship as a "global responsibility", as firms race to secure resources central to energy transition goals.
articles.title: India's Modi urges nations with critical minerals to see custodianship as 'global responsibility'

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: One person died and 57 were injured after two explosions at a liquefied petroleum gas station in the Romanian town of Crevedia near the capital Bucharest on Saturday.
articles.title: One person dead, 57 injured after explosions at Romanian gas station

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Iran's enrichment of uranium continues based on a framework established by the country's parliament, nuclear chief Mohammad Eslami said on Sunday when asked about reports regarding Tehran slowing down its 60% enrichment.
articles.title: Iran says uranium enrichment continues based on domestic law

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian investigators said on Sunday that genetic tests had confirmed that Yevgeny Prigozhin, chief of the Wagner mercenary group, was among the 10 people killed in a plane crash last Wednesday.
articles.title: Russia says genetic tests confirm Prigozhin died in plane crash

articles.author: Jasper Ward
articles.description: A shooting at a Dollar General store in Jacksonville, Florida, left four people dead on Saturday, Fox News reported.
articles.title: Four people dead in Dollar General shooting in Jacksonville

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China halved the stamp duty on stock trading effective Monday in the latest attempt to boost the struggling market as a recovery sputters in the world's second-biggest economy.
articles.title: China halves stamp duty on stock trades to boost flagging market
